A 28-year-old man died when his car collided with a truck in Gqeberha on Thursday afternoon. Police spokesperson Captain Gerda Swart said the collision between a Volvo truck and a Mazda happen at 2.10pm  at the  Addo and Maku roads intersection. Swart said  the truck driver was  assaulted and  goods  looted from the truck after the accident. Swart said the driver of the Mazda died  at the scene. “The name of the victim will be released once his next-of-kin  have been notified,” she said. Swart said the truck driver was taken from the scene with minimal injuries. HeraldLIVE 